description: Grong Sparebank, an independent savings bank, provides a range of banking products and services in Norway. It offers mutual fund savings, wealth advice, retirement savings, BSU, and savings accounts products; mortgage, construction loans, fixed-rate loans, framework loan, cottage loans, car loans, and consumer loans; refinancing the mortgage; and loans for other vehicles. The company also provides various insurance products, such as car and other vehicles, contents, dog, travel, child, valuables, home, electric scooter, house and belongings, life and health insurance; and bankID app, avtalGiro and eInvoice, pay with smartwatch, easy and contactless payment, Vips, bank and credit cards, deposit accounts, mobile payments, current accounts, mobile banking and online banking, and in-store cash services. Grong Sparebank was founded in 1862 and is headquartered in Grong, Norway.
